{"type":"message","id":"47e794fd","parentId":"d9146576","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:43:51.197Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dzkm6lk5a1u9_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 044119\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/TIC/EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- TIC Experiment is the next priority\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions, the most concrete next step is to start implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The first concrete action would be to:\r\n\r\n1. Create a script to analyze the pulse logs and extract invariants/variants\r\n2. This would involve reading the pulse logs in `logs/pulse_*.md` and analyzing them\r\n\r\nGiven I need to write a PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI as a pending task, and I need to implement the TIC classifier, let me think about the most impactful single action.\r\n\r\nThe TIC experiment requires:\r\n- Reading pulse logs\r\n- Classifying content as invariant (persistent) vs variant (ephemeral)\r\n- Measuring accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and what would be the most useful single action. The most concrete step would be to:\r\n1. Create the TIC analysis script or\r\n2. Update the state/goals.md to reflect the new Phase 1 advancement insight\r\n3. Or create the PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n\r\nGiven the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is new, I should:\r\n1. Update the goals document to reflect this collapse of Phase 1 and Phase 2\r\n2. Create a concrete experiment plan\r\n\r\nLet me look at what would be most useful. The notes say:\r\n- \"Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\"\r\n\r\nThis is a significant insight that should update the goals document. Let me also create a concrete experiment script for TIC.\r\n\r\nGiven the constraint of ONE concrete action, I'll:\r\n- Update state/goals.md to reflect the Phase 1/Phase 2 collapse and the TIC experiment next steps\r\n\r\nThis keeps the state accurate and sets up for the TIC implementation next pulse.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nPhase 1 and Phase 2 have collapsed into a unified problem (COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY), but state/goals.md still shows them as separate phases. The goals need to reflect this synthesis before implementing the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nUpdate goals document to reflect the unified Phase 1/2 collapse and the TIC experiment as the immediate next step.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: ## Pending\r\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n- [ ] Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\n## Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY (2026-03-23)\r\n- **Insight:** Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n- **New doc:** `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\r\n- **Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\r\n- **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) - test on last 20 pulse logs\r\n- **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n- **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\r\n\r\n### NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n\r\n1. **The gap IS the compression** - session boundaries are temporal hashing\r\n2. **λ encodes both** - decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\r\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** - Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\r\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** - session gaps as compression is novel and correct\r\nnew_text: ## Phase 1 COMPLETE (unified with Phase 2)\r\n- COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY: Causal discovery IS invariant compression\r\n- Full synthesis: `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\r\n\r\n## Phase 2 IN PROGRESS (unified with Phase 1)\r\n- **Experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC)\r\n- **Target:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n- **Data:** last 20 pulse logs in `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n\r\n## Pending\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy  \r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- [ ] Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n\r\n## Key Insights\r\n\r\n1. **Phase 1/Phase 2 COLLAPSE:** Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n2. **The gap IS the compression** - session boundaries are temporal hashing\r\n3. **λ encodes both** - decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\r\n4. **Three architectures, one synthesis** - Infant, TemporalAttention, Breakaway complementary\r\n5. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** - session gaps as compression is novel and correct\r\nfile: state/goals.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:41:47\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774341831196}}
